      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison at 5 flow-speed operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 operating conditions. Predicted values fall within 18% of experimental means across all points. Uncertainty in experimental measurements is discussed in the assessment narrative: pump-to-pump variability estimated at ±12% and inter-laboratory variability at ±8%, yielding a combined experimental uncertainty band that encompasses model predictions at 4 of 5 operating points. Monte Carlo sampling (n=2000) was used to propagate inlet boundary condition uncertainty through the solver; results are summarized in Section 4.3 of the assessment report.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-hemolysis-5pt"
