      "name": "Wall shear stress profile validation against PIV measurements",
      "description": "Particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements of wall shear stress in the impeller region are compared to CFD predictions. Agreement within 22% RMS deviation is observed across the measurement plane. Uncertainty in PIV measurements is noted qualitatively; optical access limitations introduce systematic bias estimated informally at less than 15% in the near-wall region. No formal UQ artifact was linked to this result; aleatory variability in the PIV ensemble (shot noise, particle seeding density variation) is described in prose in the validation report but not quantified as a structured uncertainty node."
    },
    {
